{"type":"message","id":"f32d5b16","parentId":"8c841b80","timestamp":"2026-05-28T07:08:51.624Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, it still says \"agentId is not allowed for sessions_spawn (allowed: father)\". Maybe the config change hasn't taken effect yet, or there's something else going on.\n\nLet me check - perhaps the `allowAgents` config needs to be at a different level. Let me look at the documentation again more carefully.\n\nFrom the subagents doc:\n> `agents.defaults.subagents.allowAgents`: Default configured target-agent allowlist used when the requester agent does not set its own `subagents.allowAgents`.\n\nSo this should apply when the requester agent (me, father) doesn't have its own `subagents.allowAgents` set. Since I set it in defaults, it should apply.\n\nWait, but maybe the `allowAgents` needs to be set on the specific agent's subagents config, not just defaults. Let me check.\n\nActually, the doc says:\n> `agents.list[].subagents.allowAgents`: List of configured agent ids that can be targeted via explicit `agentId` (`[\"*\"]` allows any configured target). Default: only the requester agent. If you set a list and still want the requester to spawn itself with `agentId`, include the requester id in the list.\n\nHmm, \"Default: only the requester agent\" - this is the default for agents.list[].subagents.allowAgents. When the per-agent setting is not set, it falls back to \"only the requester agent\".\n\nThe `agents.defaults.subagents.allowAgents` is the default used when the requester agent doesn't have its own setting. But since I set it in defaults, it should apply to all agents including the father agent (the requester).\n\nWait, but maybe the hot-reload hasn't picked up the changes yet? Let me check.\n\nActually, let me re-check the config file.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_krgDR4odhuQvjgLFgb7g0394","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport json\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\n    config = json.load(f)\nsa = config['agents']['defaults']['subagents']\nprint('allowAgents:', sa.get('allowAgents'))\n\""},"partialArgs":"{\"command\": \"python3 -c \\\"\\nimport json\\nwith open('/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json') as f:\\n    config = json.load(f)\\nsa = config['agents']['defaults']['subagents']\\nprint('allowAgents:', sa.get('allowAgents'))\\n\\\"\"}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":95,"output":492,"cacheRead":53120,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":393,"totalTokens":53707,"cost":{"input":0.000013300000000000001,"output":0.00013776,"cacheRead":0.0014873599999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0016384199999999998}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1779952125786,"responseId":"99ce6f07-d4ef-46c8-af96-ecce78ebd4d0"}}
