{"type":"message","id":"591bf91f","parentId":"9026aad6","timestamp":"2026-05-28T07:08:57.632Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The config is correct. Maybe it's a reload issue. Let me check if the gateway restarted or if the hot-reload picked up the changes. Let me try the openclaw gateway call to restart or check.\n\nActually, looking at the previous test I did - I used `agentId: \"father\"` in the spawn, and it worked. But now when I try `agentId: \"spirit\"`, it says \"allowed: father\".\n\nThe error message \"allowed: father\" suggests that only \"father\" is in the allow list. Maybe the hot-reload hasn't taken effect yet for this kind of config change, or maybe the gateway needs a restart for `allowAgents` to be picked up.\n\nLet me check the reload mode - it's `hybrid` by default.\n\nWait, looking at the config more carefully - maybe I need to set it per-agent rather than in defaults. Let me try to directly edit the father agent's subagents config.\n\nActually, maybe it's because I'm the father agent (agentId: father) and I can only spawn agents that are listed in my allowAgents. The `allowAgents` in `defaults.subagents` might not apply to me because I'm the requester and my own per-agent setting overrides defaults.\n\nLet me add `allowAgents: [\"*\"]` to the father agent's config specifically.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"可能热重载还没完全生效。让我直接加到 Father 的专属配置里："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_00_XV4X8nZCC1mgMAl2hk8m6052","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json","edits":[{"oldText":"      {\n        \"id\": \"father\",\n        \"workspace\": \"/root/.openclaw/workspace-father\"\n      }","newText":"      {\n        \"id\": \"father\",\n        \"workspace\": \"/root/.openclaw/workspace-father\",\n        \"subagents\": {\n          \"allowAgents\": [\"*\"]\n        }\n      }"}]},"partialArgs":"{\"path\": \"/root/.openclaw/openclaw.json\", \"edits\": [{\"oldText\":\