{"type":"custom_message","customType":"openclaw.runtime-context","content":"[media attached: /root/.openclaw/media/qqbot/downloads/06B88DD5976CD8637B3B648A3479582F_1779953173146_fa19f8.jpg (image/jpeg)]\nTo send an image back, prefer the message tool (media/path/filePath). If you must inline, use MEDIA:https://example.com/image.jpg (spaces ok, quote if needed) or a safe relative path like MEDIA:./image.jpg. Absolute and ~ paths only work when they stay inside your allowed file-read boundary; host file:// URLs are blocked. Keep caption in the text body.\n[Image]\nUser text:\n[qqbot 6687D4D2D1F8EDA5231C6809B1A26204 Thu 2026-05-28 15:26 GMT+8]\nDescription:\nThe image shows a computer screen with a terminal interface displaying logs from the \"OpenClaw\" application. The logs, timestamped around 15:20–15:22, indicate configuration errors related to an invalid `openc Claw.json` file, specifically due to an \"Invalid input\" in the `auth.profiles.dashscope:default` section. Error messages suggest running `openc Claw doctor --fix` to repair the config. A large ASCII art logo reading \"OPENCLAW\" is centered on the screen. The system appears to be Linux-based","display":false,"details":{"source":"openclaw-runtime-context"},"id":"148dccb5","parentId":"54baa5dc","timestamp":"2026-05-28T07:26:30.179Z"}
